<span id="freeTextContainer13534511869624239294"><i>The War of the End of the World</i> is a panoramic and polychromatic canvas – it is equally historical, philosophical, psychological and adventurous story and one of the deepest at that.<br/><blockquote>Do the rhetorical quarrels of bourgeois political parties have anything to do with the interests of the humble and downtrodden?</blockquote><br/>The question is posed and the entire novel is a meticulous answer to this question.<br/>There are some strange pages in the history of humankind and the novel is an endeavor to open one of such pa</span>
  <span id="freeText13534511869624239294" style="display:none"><i>The War of the End of the World</i> is a panoramic and polychromatic canvas – it is equally historical, philosophical, psychological and adventurous story and one of the deepest at that.<br /><blockquote>Do the rhetorical quarrels of bourgeois political parties have anything to do with the interests of the humble and downtrodden?</blockquote><br />The question is posed and the entire novel is a meticulous answer to this question.<br />There are some strange pages in the history of humankind and the novel is an endeavor to open one of such pages. The central figure is a magnetic person whose magnetism can’t be explained rationally but the thousands were on his side and they fought unselfishly and desperately for their misty ideals.<br />He who possesses charisma charms his followers similar to a snake staring at its helpless prey.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13534511869624239294" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

