<div id="review_661704813" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/661704813" />
    <a title="AC" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1655437-ac"><img alt="AC" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1228702469p2/1655437.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/661704813?book_show_action=true">Jul 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="AC" class="user" itemprop="url" name="AC" href="/user/show/1655437-ac">AC</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780312427986" href="/book/show/3265193-the-war-of-the-end-of-the-world">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1655437-ac?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1655437-ac?shelf=novels-spanish">novels-spanish</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer661704813" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer602741707473968453">An extremely interesting book, brilliantly executed and conceived. It is clear that this is a writer of the first order, though I do not know (I doubt, actually) that the voice is representative of Vargas Llosa&apos;s other works. <br/><br/>An historical novel, set at the end of the 19th cen., there is a certain archaism and hieratic nature in the writing which is appropriate to -- and which works, given the topic -- but which can, in the end, be fatiguing.<br/><br/>The book explores a realm of moral ambiguity, and in a</span>
  <span id="freeText602741707473968453" style="display:none">An extremely interesting book, brilliantly executed and conceived. It is clear that this is a writer of the first order, though I do not know (I doubt, actually) that the voice is representative of Vargas Llosa's other works. <br /><br />An historical novel, set at the end of the 19th cen., there is a certain archaism and hieratic nature in the writing which is appropriate to -- and which works, given the topic -- but which can, in the end, be fatiguing.<br /><br />The book explores a realm of moral ambiguity, and in a fashion that is profound. But the issue is resolved too early, with the result that the book becomes, in my opinion, *much* too long, and (as a result of this early resolution) veers even into melodrama. While the characters are drawn with great sympathy and with nuance, I can not fully empathize with their vision.<br /><br />But that said, it is still the length and tedium and melodrama of a writer, as I've said, of the first order.</span>
  <a data-text-id="602741707473968453" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


