<div id="review_1401646764" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1401646764" />
    <a title="Sam" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18954745-sam"><img alt="Sam" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1401646764?book_show_action=true">Sep 26, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sam" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sam" href="/user/show/18954745-sam">Sam</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780312427986" href="/book/show/3265193-the-war-of-the-end-of-the-world">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1401646764" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6629440167492638781">The story of a doomed catholic uprising in the sertao in 19th century NE Brazil. Flocking to the town of Canudos, drawn by the magnetism of the ascetic wandering figure known as the Counselor, a mishmash of freaks, murderers, bandits, mystics, communists and otherwise downtrodden masess begin an uprising against the newly formed Brazilian republic. Fearing the republics secular posture, the religious fanatics call for a return of the monarchy and prepare for the inevitable confrontation with the</span>
  <span id="freeText6629440167492638781" style="display:none">The story of a doomed catholic uprising in the sertao in 19th century NE Brazil. Flocking to the town of Canudos, drawn by the magnetism of the ascetic wandering figure known as the Counselor, a mishmash of freaks, murderers, bandits, mystics, communists and otherwise downtrodden masess begin an uprising against the newly formed Brazilian republic. Fearing the republics secular posture, the religious fanatics call for a return of the monarchy and prepare for the inevitable confrontation with the armies sent to pacify them.<br /><br />This book captures the feel of the sertao and its ignorant, superstitious, savage and proud inhabitants. Full of fantastic characters like Pajeu, Satan Joao, the little blessed one, Galileo Gall, the Lion of Natuba, and the hard nosed army colonel sent to defeat them. When asked why they didn't flee the oncoming army, the residents of Canudos replied, they already had run, to Canudos, and there was nowhere left to run to. The battles in the deserts of northern Brasil are brutal and savage as the peasants fight for their lives and souls against the troops of the heathen republic.<br /><br />My only concern with this book was how dry it read and I fear that perhaps a better translation might be available somewhere. Seems like something is a little off. Anyways, really great to read a story based in Bahia and I enjoyed it immensely.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6629440167492638781" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


