<div id="review_548729980" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/548729980" />
    <a title="Robbie Bruens" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4316993-robbie-bruens"><img alt="Robbie Bruens" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1348966919p2/4316993.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/548729980?book_show_action=true">Feb 28, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Robbie Bruens" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Robbie Bruens" href="/user/show/4316993-robbie-bruens">Robbie Bruens</a>
      </span>

          added it


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/17449222-the-war-of-the-end-of-the-world">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4316993-robbie-bruens?shelf=novel">novel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4316993-robbie-bruens?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4316993-robbie-bruens?shelf=latin-american">latin-american</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4316993-robbie-bruens?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4316993-robbie-bruens?shelf=translations">translations</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4316993-robbie-bruens?shelf=war">war</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer548729980" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12258878012415957401">Nobel Laureate Vargas Llosa recounts the epic story of the Canudos rebellion in fin-de-siècle Brazil in an interminable novel that resembles an impeccably detailed outline for a costume drama miniseries. There are so many characters and settings that the book occasionally feels like studying for an exam. As someone with a bachelors&apos; degree in history and a longtime intense fascination with tales of the past, I would imagine I am exactly the target audience for this type of book. Alas, while ther</span>
  <span id="freeText12258878012415957401" style="display:none">Nobel Laureate Vargas Llosa recounts the epic story of the Canudos rebellion in fin-de-siècle Brazil in an interminable novel that resembles an impeccably detailed outline for a costume drama miniseries. There are so many characters and settings that the book occasionally feels like studying for an exam. As someone with a bachelors' degree in history and a longtime intense fascination with tales of the past, I would imagine I am exactly the target audience for this type of book. Alas, while there are many dozens of indelible passages to be found here, the sum of this novel's innumerable parts add up to a curiously sprawling yet dull expanse. Perhaps the characters bleed together too readily, or Vargas Llosa's propensity for describing events from many different perspectives just doesn't reveal much in the way of new insights but rather feels repetitious. Given how long I have spent with this book (nearly a year, as I began reading it when I was actually traveling in Vargas Llosa's home country of Peru last year), I could probably expound for quite some time on what didn't work very well, as well as the book's many pleasures. Instead, I'll just say that The Time of the Hero is an excellent book with all the emotional depth and structural sophistication that this book lacked. I hope that when I read more of Vargas Llosa's books in the future, they hew closer to the febrile genius of The Time of the Hero and less to the wasted genius of The War of the End of the World.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12258878012415957401" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

